channel.title: Starting up a team for a new project
channel.description:
I am starting up a team for my new server. I am waiting until the project is officially started before I make the server name. It is PI based using the Nividia source. I haven't changed much yet but I have spawned all the custom items and will be deleting the non-needed ones and fixing the glitched ones. I will be making new shops and once the team is started I will explore the source and find any bugs/glitches that need to be fixed. If you would like to help with this project post your application in this format:
Name: Age: Java knowledge: 1/10 What are you applying for: (coder/brainstormer/graphic designer/website designer/advertiser) Years with java: Will you stay dedicated to the server?: Why should we choose you?:
Host Me
Coder Me None
Brainstormers None None
Website designer None None
Graphics designer None
Advertisers None None None
Thank you all for helping and giving feedback to this post

item.title: Starting up a team for a new project
item.dc:creator: @TheHolyGrail TheHolyGrail
item.description:
@TheHolyGrail wrote:

Vexillum:

Ok will do, but could you maybe give me some info on how to take a screenshot? Like I know how to do it with paint and stuff but all I know how to do is take the screenshot of the computer screen then go to paint and edit it… is there a way where you can choose like one region of the computer screen and take a pic of it?

On your keyboard there is a button that says “PrtSc” or “Print Screen” or something like that. Click that and head on into paint.

Click Edit-Paste and there you go. Just crop it and upload it to photobucket.com

Cheers.
